The Los Angeles International Airport was evacuated due to gunfire in one of its terminals.
An unidentified man opened fire in the third terminal at 09:30 local time on Friday, November 1 (20:30 Moscow time).
Security evacuated employees and passengers of the second and third terminals.
According to preliminary data, the man directed fire from a high-powered rifle.
Several people, including an employee of the U.S. transportation security administration, were injured.
Police returned fire and detained the perpetrator.
He is slightly wounded.
